{
  "text": "Further disparities were found when swimming proficiency was analyzed by ethnicity. Twice as many European and Maori students claimed that they could swim more than 100 m than Pasifika and Asian students (see Table 1 ). One third of Asian students (32%) and more than one quarter of Pasifika students (27%) thought that they could swim less than 25 m, giving them little protection in the event of either intentional or unintentional immersion in open water. The lack of swimming competency found among ethnic minorities in this study is consistent with findings in overseas studies that have associated high drowning incidence among ethnic minorities with poor swimming ability [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
